HEADWORD: Exportability
<hw>Ex*port`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or state of being suitable for exportation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To increase the <qex>exportability</qex> of native goods.</q>
<rj><qau>J. P. Peters.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exportable</ent>⟦br⟧
